The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																																																		A fire broke out in a solution-making factory in Tiljalas Avinash Chowdhury Lane around 4.25pm on Wednesday. Three fire tenders rushed to the spot and doused the flames after three hours. No one was injured, but the factory was gutted. Fire brigade officials said there were no fire-safety measures at the factory, which led to the blaze spreading rapidly on the premises. It is suspected that the fire originated from an electrical short-circuit.																																																		A fire broke out in a house in Birati, on the northern fringes of the city, on Wednesday morning. Two tenders went to the spot around 10am and the blaze was brought under control after two hours. No one was injured. Fire brigade sources said the fire had originated from a kitchen appliance.																																																		Indrani Sarkar, daughter of state water resources minister Nanda Gopal Bhattacharya, was injured in a car accident on Tuesday evening. Police said the driver of Sarkars car, moving along VIP Road, lost control and hit a divider near the PWD office. She was injured in her head and chest and was taken to a nursing home.																																																		Purabi Roychowdhury, 55, committed suicide by setting herself on fire in her Bibeknagar house, in Kasba, on Wednesday morning. She died while being taken to a nursing home. An unnatural death case has been started. Purabi had been suffering from cancer. No suicide note was found.																																																		The Howrah unit of the pollution control board (PCB) will depute two teams of observers on Diwali to monitor the use of amplifiers and bursting of illegal firecrackers in and around silence zones.																																																		The state government has received Rs 615 crore under Jawaharlal Nehru National Urban Renewal Mission, an official in the state urban development and municipal affairs department said on Wednesday. The money will be spent on infrastructure upgrade in the city. 
